|~ ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   qlang LSP showcase

   Open this file in VS Code with the qlang extension active
   to exercise every LSP feature:
     1. Ctrl+Click — Go to Definition
     2. Hover — operand docs, projections, keywords
     3. Ctrl+Shift+O — Outline (all bindings)
     4. Shift+F12 — Find References
     5. Type inside parens — Signature Help
     6. Ctrl+Space — Completion

   This file is one pipeline. Comments between sections act
   as identity steps, and each literal replaces pipeValue. ~|


|~| ── 1. Hover ──────────────────────────────────────────
|~| Hover over count, filter, sort, union, reify, if,
|~| coalesce, sortWith, asc, desc to see manifest docs.

[1 2 3 4 5] | count

|~| Hover /name → "projection /name — extracts value from Map"
|~| Hover :age  → "keyword :age"

{:name "alice" :age 30} | /name


|~| ── 2. Go to Definition ───────────────────────────────
|~| Ctrl+Click on a user binding → its let/as declaration.
|~| Ctrl+Click on a builtin → manifest.qlang.

|~~| Doubles a number via partial mul. ~~|
let(:double, mul(2))

|~~| Triples a number via partial mul. ~~|
let(:triple, mul(3))

|~| Ctrl+Click on double below → jumps to the let above
[1 2 3] * double

|~| Ctrl+Click on triple below → jumps to the let above
[10 20] * triple

|~| Ctrl+Click on count below → jumps to manifest.qlang
[1 2 3] | count


|~| ── 3. Shadowing ──────────────────────────────────────
|~| When an identifier is rebound, go-to-definition jumps
|~| to the LAST visible declaration, not the first.

let(:x, 1)
|~| x here resolves to 1
let(:x, 99)
|~| Ctrl+Click on x below → jumps to let(:x, 99)
x


|~| ── 4. Fork isolation ─────────────────────────────────
|~| Bindings inside (parens), [vecs], {maps}, #{sets} are
|~| fork-isolated — invisible outside the fork boundary.

(42 | as(:inner) | inner)
|~| inner is visible inside the paren group above.
|~| It is NOT visible outside the parens.


|~| ── 5. Find References ────────────────────────────────
|~| Shift+F12 shows all occurrences: declaration + uses.

let(:greet, prepend("hello "))
| "world" | greet | as(:greeted1)
| "qlang" | greet | as(:greeted2)
|~| Shift+F12 on greet → 3 hits (1 decl + 2 uses)


|~| ── 6. Outline ────────────────────────────────────────
|~| Ctrl+Shift+O → let bindings show as Function,
|~| as bindings show as Variable.

let(:votingAge, filter(/age | gte(18)))
| 42 | as(:answer)
|~| Outline lists: double, triple, x, greet, greeted1,
|~| greeted2, votingAge, answer


|~| ── 7. Signature Help ─────────────────────────────────
|~| Type inside parens of an operand to see its signature.
|~| Active parameter highlights on comma.

[{:name "a" :age 25} {:name "b" :age 15}]
  | filter(/age | gte(18))
  * /name

|~| Edit inside add(/x, /y) below — second param highlights
{:x 10 :y 3} | add(/x, /y)


|~| ── 8. Completion ─────────────────────────────────────
|~| Ctrl+Space → every langRuntime entry (67 operands
|~| including let, as, error, isError) + user bindings
|~| visible at the cursor position.

let(:myHelper, mul(10))
|~| Ctrl+Space here → myHelper alongside every builtin


|~| ── 9. Diagnostics ────────────────────────────────────
|~| Syntax errors show as red squiggles in real time.
|~| Try typing something invalid to see a parse error.


|~| ── 10. Comments ───────────────────────────────────────
|~| Four comment forms, all syntax-highlighted:
|~|   line plain, block plain, line doc, block doc.
|~| Doc comments attach to the next let/as binding.

|~~| Computes the absolute value via conditional negation. ~~|
let(:abs, if(lt(0), mul(-1)))

|~~ Surround a string with a prefix and suffix.
    Parametric conduit with two captured parameters. ~~|
let(:@surround, [:pfx, :sfx], prepend(pfx) | append(sfx))

|~| Ctrl+Click on @surround → jumps to the let above
"world" | @surround("[", "]")


|~| ── 11. Effect markers ────────────────────────────────
|~| @-prefixed identifiers carry the effect-marker sigil.
|~| The @ gets distinct highlighting from the name.


|~| ── 12. Comparator composition ────────────────────────
|~| sortWith + asc/desc + firstNonZero compose declaratively.
|~| Hover each operand to see its docs.

[{:name "c" :age 30} {:name "a" :age 25} {:name "b" :age 25}]
  | sortWith([asc(/age), desc(/name)] | firstNonZero)
  * /name


|~| ── 13. Fail-apply combinator ─────────────────────────
|~| `!|` routes its step to the fail-track: it fires only
|~| when pipeValue is an error value, exposing the error's
|~| materialized descriptor Map to the step on the right.
|~| On a success pipeValue it deflects as identity
|~| pass-through. The tmLanguage grammar scopes `!|` as
|~| keyword.operator.fail-apply.qlang so themes can colour
|~| it distinctly from the success-track `|`.

|~| Direct fail-apply: read :kind off a runtime error
"hello" | add(1) !| /kind

|~| Leading !| prefix inside a filter predicate —
|~| per-element dispatch into the fail-track
[1 "x" 3] * add(10) | filter(!| /thrown | eq(:AddLeftNotNumber))

|~| Trail continuity across re-lift — | error re-wraps the
|~| enriched descriptor and a later !| reads the
|~| accumulated :trail Vec
!{:kind :oops} | count !| union({:request "r-1"}) | error | add(1) !| /trail
